title: SFH on columbariums
content_text:
p>
    Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the 
    Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, at a media session in Beijing 
    this afternoon (November 3): Reporter: (on regulation of private columbariums) Secretary for Food and Health: We are very happy that the court has made the 
    right decision and the right ruling. We have warned operators of these 
    columbariums many times that they should comply with the planning and land 
    lease conditions. We have also cautioned all the consumers that if they try

lease conditions. We have also cautioned all the consumers that if they try 
    to buy niches from those columbarium operators, they should know which type 
    of columbarium they are buying. We have the List A and List B (information 
    on private columbarium) that are clearly prepared by the Development Bureau 
    so that consumers should know whether they are legal or not. For those that 
    are in List B and are trying to being regularised, they need to go through 
    the procedures and submit applications through the relevant departments. It

the procedures and submit applications through the relevant departments. It 
    is very important for the public to understand that the Government is trying 
    to do everything to regularise this particular supply of columbariums. But 
    at the same time, there are certain areas that we will never be able to 
    accept, especially those in the residential areas. The Government is also 
    supplying a further number of niches within the next 12 months or so. We

supplying a further number of niches within the next 12 months or so. We plan to have at least 40,000 more niches next year in Wo Hop Shek. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
